                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I spend my days as a magician these days so I have been spending some time perusing the Mage Compendium forums.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=17632" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">A thread</span></a> came up recently there about the charm nerf.  It was interesting to see the hate some mages had for enchanters, because they felt supplanted by the charming enchanter's pets and their DPS.  Invariably, all of these chanter-haters had little or no understanding of the risk involved, giving it lip service at best (like SOE) and not even acknowledging the risk or XP penalty in most cases.
<br />

<br />
Those of you out there who play other classes, have you seen any similar feedback from other classes about the OOW charm changes?
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Added link to Mage forum thread.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
